rComments: He is literally the best professor I ever had. He tests heavy (three 1000-word essays for final) and expects you to use information in class. So take notes and go to class if you want a good grade. He is very friendly and love to talk in office hour. I hope he can teach more courses in STG campus!

Professor Yaniszewski is one of the best prof. He expands your knowledge and delivers lectures in a way that's understandable and engaging. I really enjoyed going to class and listening to his (sometimes) needless anecdotes about things. He's also really fun to talk to and personable during office hours. I highly recommend his class.
amazing prof, I really wish we also teaches on st george campus

rComments: Nice professor but distracted easily. Course grading scheme is unnecessary. Essay worth 25%, same with midterm but expects a lot for midterm and final. rComments: Funny and engaging prof. He made the course content really interesting and easy to understand. Best class I've taken at U of T so far, made me love pol sci.

Using modern day examples to engage the class and relate to the modern world.  Explains theories and concepts using political science lingo whilst providing real life examples which are then explained in more simple lingo to illustrate a point.  Often exaggerates examples to make a point or make you think twice about what is truly going on. Was Fun

Yaniszewski is one of the best profs I've had so far. His lectures are long, but he makes the material interesting and he's got a sense of humour.  If you take good notes and attend all the lectures, you will do really well. Tutorial attendance and participation is an easy 15% of the mark.

rComments: Professor Yaniszewski presents and great breadth of information that is not posted online, therefore it is essential to go to class. The assignments have a very specific grading criteria, however, if you seek assistance he provides great extra help. The best trait about him is that he is funny and presents great examples in an engaging manner.

Amazing PoliSci prof. I started this course hating and not caring about int'l relations. Only a few lectures in, he had my mind changed. He is extremely knowledgeable, has interesting viewpoints, can counter-argue anything (including his own viewpoint!), and manages to discuss difficult info while making it easy to comprehend. Lecture is key.

Class attendance and kick-ass note taking skills will make or break you. Long lectures with LOADS of information, suggest laptop if you want to avoid carpal tunnel.  Readings are not necessary,  test are fair but require detailed knowledge  of case studies. Long final essay (15-20pg) tough grading, start asap, do not leave till last minute.

Very interesting, clear lectures. Attendance and good note taking are a must. Readings are assigned but only for your benefithelp understand material. 2 tests should do fine if you review your detailed notes. 2 papers 8-10 pgs straightforward and he's always there to meet with you if you need help. Recommend.
